  intro y; simp
  intro h
  rcases h i with ⟨x, xAi, fxeq⟩
  use x; constructor
  · intro i'
    rcases h i' with ⟨x', x'Ai, fx'eq⟩
    have : f x = f x' := by rw [fxeq, fx'eq]
    have : x = x' := injf this
    rw [this]
    exact x'Ai
  exact fxeq

  rintro y h; rcases h i with ⟨x, xAi, rfl⟩
  exact ⟨x, fun i' => let ⟨x', x'Ai, hx'⟩ := h i' in injf hx'.symm ▸ x'Ai, rfl⟩

    _ = y := by rw [sq_sqrt ynonneg]

decl: theorem Cantor : ∀ f : α → Set α, ¬Surjective f
og_raw:
theorem Cantor : ∀ f : α → Set α, ¬Surjective f := by
  intro f surjf
  let S := { i | i ∉ f i }
  rcases surjf S with ⟨j, h⟩
  have h₁ : j ∉ f j := by
    intro h'
    have : j ∉ f j := by rwa [h] at h'
    contradiction
  have h₂ : j ∈ S := h₁
  have h₃ : j ∉ S := by rwa [h] at h₁
  contradiction
new_raw:
theorem Cantor : ∀ f : α → Set α, ¬Surjective f  := by
  intro f surjf
  let S := { i | i ∉ f i }
  rcases surjf S with ⟨j, h⟩
  have : j ∉ f j ↔ j ∉ S := by rwa [h]
  exact this.2 (this.1 (λ hj, (this.1 hj) hj))
